    "client_msg_id": "2da39aa2-d622-4f73-931f-3d30fedbfea0",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "As I go slowly my way through the kernel syllabus, I find gems like this one: \"The practice of software begins to resemble closely the practice of memoria and, specifically, the <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giulio_Camillo|memory theatres of Camillo>, which constitute memory as a public space; a kind of virtual architecture for an incomplete image of the world. *Software begins to look like the closest medium to memory itself we have produced*.\" <https://www.kernel.community/en/learn/module-3/remember/#memory-only-exists-when-distributed>\nWhat do you think? How do do you personally perceive Software as Memory?",
    "user": "UJFN50C00",
    "ts": "1668766856.536659",
    "blocks": [
